          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>St Thomas</placeName>
                                        <date>6 Sep 1852</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. I Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">My Dr Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">I am in receipt of your various<lb/> letters with
                                        the missing Occidents &amp; those up to
                                        <date>August</date>.<lb/> I found them very interesting—I
                                        delivered your letter to <persName>Mr<lb/>
                                                  Simmonds</persName> who is as you will perceive
                                        alive. I spoke to one of<lb/> his subscribers as to the
                                        payments, he only owes for the present<lb/> year.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The Government have extended to these
                                                  <placeName>Islands</placeName> a<lb/>
                                        representative assembly to be held yearly at <placeName>St
                                                  Croix</placeName>, the vote for<lb/>
                                        Representation of the three <placeName>Islands</placeName>
                                        to be held in at each<lb/>
                                        <placeName>Island</placeName> on the same day. The Governor
                                        who <add>?</add> the day<lb/> of election resides at
                                                  <placeName>St Croix</placeName> which
                                                  <del>he</del> is head Quarters,<lb/> the day of
                                        the first election was <add>?</add> by him for
                                                  <date>Saturday<lb/> the 28</date> &amp; it was
                                        announced in our news paper on the <date>22<hi rend="sup"
                                                  >d</hi></date>. I<lb/> immediately wrote a
                                        Christian friend at <placeName>St Croix</placeName> to
                                        call<lb/> on His <add>?</add> for me &amp; state that I was
                                        persuaded he<lb/> did not recollect that
                                                  <date>Saturday</date> was the Jewish<lb/>
                                        <date>Sabbath</date> &amp; that would preclude many
                                        Israelites <del>from</del><lb/> voting, that I was appointed
                                        one of the Judges <del>of</del> at the<lb/> Poll which I
                                        would have to decline. His Excellency<lb/> replied to my
                                        friend that he saw the propriety of<lb/> altering the day
                                        &amp; <add>?</add> it for <date>Monday the 30
                                        August</date><lb/> will you insert this in the Chronicle in
                                        good stile. I<lb/> think it should commence with “Justice
                                        &amp; liberality.” I see<lb/>
                                        <add>?</add> by experience, that if we respect ourselves we
                                        will<lb/> be respected for your information I had 32 votes
                                        &amp; would<lb/> have been one of the Representatives had
                                        not the Directors of<lb/> the Bank used their influence with
                                        the voters, to prevent my</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p><sic>my</sic> return, stating as the reason that my services were<lb/>
                                        <sic>indispensible</sic> to the Bank. Many happy holy
                                        days—</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Yours truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <persName role="author">A Wolff</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>I am happy to find you have<lb/> progressed so well with the Bible,
                                        the type appears<lb/> to be very good &amp; the printing
                                        distinct</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Mr I Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Philada</placeName>
                              </p>
